{"name": "ctitools", "metadata": {"name": "ctitools", "version": "0.4.17", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 1 - Planning", "Environment :: Console", "Intended Audience :: End Users/Desktop", "License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "License :: Other/Proprietary License", "Natural Language :: German", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13", "Topic :: Utilities"], "home_page": "https://python.xn--hllmanns-n4a.de/ctitools/", "license": "BSD 3", "documentation_url": "https://www.xn--hllmanns-n4a.de/python/ctitools/", "dependencies": ["rich", "typing-extensions"], "summary": "Work with cti index files for the Heise papers c't and iX", "upload_time": 1732740574}, "documentation": ["# Ctitools\n\nWork with cti index files for the Heise papers c\u2019t and iX\n\n## Description\n\nThis project provides different tool for processing index files from\nHeise papers c\u2019t and iX.\n\nSaving the current base dataset, downloaded from Heise and extractng to\ndata, the command\n\n```console\n> cti2bibtex data/inhalt.frm result.bibtex\n```\n\ncreates a `.bib` file with 82100 entries. Importing this result in\nZotero took more than 28h and use more than 7GB of RAM.\n\n`cti2bibtex` works with the zip files directly now, so the commands\n\n```console\n> cti2bibtex ctin2328.zip\n> cti2bibtex register-kurz.zip\n```\n\ncreate the files `ctin2328.bib` and `register-kurz.bib`.\n\n## Installation\n\n`ctitools` are on pypi now, so\n\n```console\n> pip install ctitools\n```\n\ninstalls the last version.\n\nIt can also be installed from the source repository on gitlab\n\n```console\n> pip install git+https://gitlab.com/berhoel/python/ctitools.git\n```\n\n## Documentation\n\nDocumentation can be found [here](https://python.h\u00f6llmanns.de/ctitools/)\n\n## Authors\n\n- Berthold H\u00f6llmann \\<<mailto:berthold@xn--hllmanns-n4a.de>>\n\n## Project status\n\nThe projects works for converting the `cti` and `frm` file, provided\nby Heise, to `bib` files.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "berhoel", "documentation": ["Initialization for berhoel python namespace packages."], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "berhoel.__date__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "berhoel.__author__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "berhoel.__copyright__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "berhoel.__credits__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "berhoel.__maintainer__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "berhoel.__email__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "berhoel.__path__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "berhoel.annotations", "xref": {"fqname": "__future__.annotations", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "berhoel.ctitools.cti2bibtex.tests.test_base", "documentation": ["Basic tests for generating BibTex entries from c't and iX articles."], "functions": [{"name": "berhoel.ctitools.cti2bibtex.tests.test_base.test_with_shorttitle", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Test correct generation of BiBTeX file entry."]}, {"name": "berhoel.ctitools.cti2bibtex.tests.test_base.test_without_shorttitle", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Test correct generation of BiBTeX file entry."]}], "variables": [{"name": "berhoel.ctitools.cti2bibtex.tests.test_base.__date__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "berhoel.ctitools.cti2bibtex.tests.test_base.__author__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "berhoel.ctitools.cti2bibtex.tests.test_base.__copyright__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "berhoel.ctitools.cti2bibtex.tests.test_base.__credits